# 💽 RAID & Disk Types – Quick Cheat Sheet

---

## 🧠 Quick Memory

* **Simple = normal**
  → Isang disk lang, walang speed, walang backup

* **Spanned = bigger**
  → Pinagsama disks para lumaki storage
  → ❌ 1 disk fail = lahat data mawawala

* **RAID 0 = fast but risky**
  → ⚡ Fast: hinahati ang data sa maraming disk (sabay-sabay read/write)
  → ❌ Risky: walang backup, 1 disk fail = lahat data lost

* **RAID 1 = safe**
  → 🛡️ May copy (mirror) ang data sa 2 disks
  → ✔ Kahit masira 1 disk, safe pa data
  → ❌ 50% lang usable space

* **RAID 5 = balanced**
  → ⚡ May speed (striping) + 🛡️ may protection (parity)
  → ✔ Kayang mag-survive ng 1 disk failure
  → ❌ Mas mabagal write

---

## 🔥 One-Line Summary

* RAID 0 → mabilis pero delikado
* RAID 1 → safe kasi may kopya
* RAID 5 → balance ng speed at protection

---

## 🎯 Teaching Tip

"If important ang data → RAID 1 or RAID 5
If speed lang kailangan → RAID 0"


